    <description>The spacecraft is designed as an octagonal prism measuring about 1.7 meters per side. It features four fixed gallium arsenide solar panels arranged like a windmill, and a 1.5-meter fixed X-band high-gain radio antenna with a magnetometer attached. An X-ray solar monitor is located on the forward deck, while other instruments are positioned on the aft deck. Most electronics and the propulsion module are housed internally.</description>
